# Declarations

## Basics

Declaring a primitive or an object is quite straight forward:
@``` decl0.gw
int i;
Object o;
<<< i, " ", o >>>;
@```
@hide make -s decl0.test

## Declaring a reference

@``` decl1.gw
Object ref ref;
<<< "Reference points to no object yet: ", ref >>>;
#!Object o @=> ref;
new Object @=> ref;
<<< "But now it does: ", ref >>>;
@```
@hide make -s decl1.test

## Arrays

### array as refs

@``` decl2.gw
int ref[];
<<< ref >>>;
new int[2] @=> ref;
<<< ref >>>;
@```
@hide make -s decl2.test
